        <section id="use-cases">
            <h2>Purpose & Applications</h2>
            <div class="use-cases">
                <div class="case-card">
                    <h3>Loop Reconstruction</h3>
                    <p>Isolate the "knock" of a kick and the "snap" of a snare from a full loop. Use SUB and LOW bands for kick sustain and HI-M for the snare snap, while muting the "mud" in BODY and LO-M bands.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="case-card">
                    <h3>Low-End Mastering Tightness</h3>
                    <p>Place on a master bus to gate only the SUB band. Sync the threshold so the gate only opens during kick hits, silencing rumbley bass in the gaps to create massive headroom and a tighter club sound.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="case-card">
                    <h3>Vocal De-Reverb</h3>
                    <p>Target the Mid and Lo-Mid bands to strip away room reflections and muddy reverb tails. Tighten up "wet" vocal recordings while keeping the high-end air clear and natural.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="case-card">
                    <h3>Precision Noise Removal</h3>
                    <p>Silence hiss or rumble in specific frequency pockets without touching the core characteristics of your audio signal. Total spectral isolation for forensic cleanup.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="case-card">
                    <h3>Drum Bleed Isolation</h3>
                    <p>Perfect for multi-track drum kits. Strip cymbal wash from snare mics or kick-drum bleed from tom mics by gating only the specific frequency bands where the bleed resides.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="case-card">
                    <h3>Creative Sound Design</h3>
                    <p>Transform static loops into rhythmic patterns. Use unipolar visualization to sculpt completely new dynamic textures across the spectrum, turning pads into pulsing rhythms.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="install">
            <h2>How to Install</h2>
